{
  "text": "At early times (\u03c4 of order \u03c9 \u22121 ) and for a close to \u03c9 or smaller, the non-Markovian terms induce strong oscillations and dominate over the Markovian terms. At later times and for \u03b1 < \u0393 convergence to equilibrium is also dominated by the non-Markovian terms, and the relaxation time is of the order of a \u22121 rather than \u0393 \u22121 . Non-Markovian effects are absent in the regime of high accelerations a > \u03c9 [CITATION_1] .",
